            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 shadow-sm mb-10">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-800 mb-4">A. Variables in Python</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-4">A variable is a reserved memory location to store values. In Python, you do not need to declare a variable's type (like <code>int</code> or <code>float</code> in C++). The type is automatically assigned based on the value you give it.</p>
                
                <div class="flex items-start gap-4 bg-purple-50 border border-purple-100 p-4 rounded-xl shadow-sm mb-6">
                    <div class="bg-purple-200 w-10 h-10 rounded-full flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-purple-700">
                        <i class="fa-solid fa-brain"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-purple-800 font-bold mb-1 text-sm">Easy Word Explanation</h4>
                        <p class="text-purple-900 text-sm leading-relaxed">Think of a variable as a labeled storage box. If you write <code>age = 20</code>, you created a box labeled "age" and put the number 20 inside it.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-3 text-lg border-b pb-2">Types of Variables / Data Types:</h4>
                <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                    <div class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-xl border border-slate-100 text-sm">
                        <strong class="text-blue-700 block mb-1">Integers (int)</strong>
                        <span class="text-slate-600">Whole numbers. (e.g., <code class="text-slate-800 font-bold">a = 10</code>)</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-xl border border-slate-100 text-sm">
                        <strong class="text-blue-700 block mb-1">Floating-Point (float)</strong>
                        <span class="text-slate-600">Decimal numbers. (e.g., <code class="text-slate-800 font-bold">pi = 3.14</code>)</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-xl border border-slate-100 text-sm">
                        <strong class="text-blue-700 block mb-1">String (str)</strong>
                        <span class="text-slate-600">Text enclosed in quotes. (e.g., <code class="text-slate-800 font-bold">name = "SBTE"</code>)</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-xl border border-slate-100 text-sm">
                        <strong class="text-blue-700 block mb-1">Boolean (bool)</strong>
                        <span class="text-slate-600">True or False values. (e.g., <code class="text-slate-800 font-bold">is_valid = True</code>)</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-800 mb-4">B. The Print() Function <span class="bg-red-100 text-red-700 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-[10px] uppercase ml-1 align-middle">PYQ</span></h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-4">The <code>print()</code> function prints the specified message to the screen.</p>
            
            <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-xl p-5 mb-10 shadow-md font-mono text-sm code-block border-l-4 border-l-blue-500">
                <span class="text-slate-400"># Example Program:</span><br/>
                <span class="text-sky-300">name</span> = <span class="text-amber-300">"Diploma Student"</span><br/>
                <span class="text-sky-300">semester</span> = <span class="text-purple-400">6</span><br/>
                <span class="text-emerald-400">print</span>(<span class="text-amber-300">"Hello"</span>, <span class="text-sky-300">name</span>)<br/>
                <span class="text-emerald-400">print</span>(<span class="text-amber-300">"You are in semester:"</span>, <span class="text-sky-300">semester</span>)
            </div>

            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-800 to-slate-900 text-white p-8 rounded-3xl shadow-xl relative overflow-hidden mb-12">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-slash absolute right-[-20px] top-[-20px] text-[12rem] text-white opacity-5"></i>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-400 mb-4 relative z-10">C. Escape Character Sequence <span class="bg-red-500 text-white text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded uppercase tracking-wider ml-1 shadow-sm">6-Mark PYQ</span></h3>
                
                <div class="space-y-4 relative z-10 text-sm">
                    <p><strong class="text-amber-200">Definition:</strong> An escape character is a backslash <code class="bg-white/20 px-1 rounded">\</code> followed by the character you want to insert. It is used to insert characters into a string that are normally illegal or difficult to type, such as a newline, a tab, or a double quote inside a string.</p>
                    <p><strong class="text-amber-200">Why it is used:</strong> If you write <code class="bg-rose-900/60 text-rose-200 px-1 rounded">print("He said "Hello" to me")</code>, Python will throw an error because of the extra quotes. Escape characters fix this: <code class="bg-emerald-900/60 text-emerald-200 px-1 rounded">print("He said \"Hello\" to me")</code>.</p>
                    
                    <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mt-6 border-b border-white/20 pb-2">Two Examples (PYQ):</h4>
                    
                    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                        <div class="bg-white/10 p-5 rounded-xl border border-white/10">
