            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1504639725590-34d0984388bd?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200" alt="Data Nodes Network" class="w-full h-64 object-cover rounded-3xl shadow-sm mb-10" />

            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 shadow-sm mb-12">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-800 mb-4">A. Python Tuple <span class="bg-red-100 text-red-700 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-[10px] uppercase ml-1 align-middle">PYQ</span></h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 mb-4"><strong>Definition:</strong> A Tuple is an ordered collection of items separated by commas and enclosed in round brackets <code>()</code>.</p>
                
                <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">Properties of Tuple:</h4>
                <ul class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 text-sm text-slate-600 mb-6">
                    <li class="bg-slate-50 p-3 rounded border border-slate-100"><strong class="text-indigo-700">Ordered:</strong> The items have a defined order that will not change.</li>
                    <li class="bg-slate-50 p-3 rounded border border-slate-100"><strong class="text-rose-600">Immutable (Unchangeable):</strong> Once a tuple is created, you cannot change, add, or remove items.</li>
                    <li class="bg-slate-50 p-3 rounded border border-slate-100"><strong class="text-indigo-700">Allows Duplicates:</strong> Tuples can have items with the same value.</li>
                    <li class="bg-slate-50 p-3 rounded border border-slate-100"><strong class="text-indigo-700">Indexed:</strong> Elements are accessed using index numbers starting from 0.</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="bg-emerald-50 p-3 rounded-lg border border-emerald-100 text-sm text-emerald-900 mb-6 inline-block">
                    <strong><i class="fa-solid fa-satellite-dish mr-1"></i> Importance in IoT:</strong> Used to store fixed data that shouldn't be altered by accident, like the static GPS coordinates of a sensor node.
                </div>

                <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-3 text-lg border-b pb-2">Python Program (Create and Access Tuple):</h4>
                <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-xl p-5 shadow-md font-mono text-sm code-block border-l-4 border-l-emerald-500">
                    <span class="text-slate-400"># 1. Creating a Tuple</span><br/>
                    <span class="text-sky-300">sensor_data</span> = (<span class="text-purple-400">25.5</span>, <span class="text-purple-400">60</span>, <span class="text-amber-300">"Active"</span>)<br/><br/>
                    
                    <span class="text-slate-400"># 2. Accessing elements using indexing</span><br/>
                    <span class="text-sky-300">temperature</span> = <span class="text-sky-300">sensor_data</span>[<span class="text-purple-400">0</span>] <span class="text-slate-500"># Index 0 gets the first item</span><br/>
                    <span class="text-sky-300">status</span> = <span class="text-sky-300">sensor_data</span>[<span class="text-purple-400">2</span>] &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="text-slate-500"># Index 2 gets the third item</span><br/><br/>
                    
                    <span class="text-emerald-400">print</span>(<span class="text-amber-300">"Temperature is:"</span>, <span class="text-sky-300">temperature</span>)<br/>
                    <span class="text-emerald-400">print</span>(<span class="text-amber-300">"Sensor Status is:"</span>, <span class="text-sky-300">status</span>)
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-10">
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 mb-3">B. Python Dictionary</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 mb-3"><strong>Definition:</strong> A Dictionary is an unordered collection of data stored as <code>Key:Value</code> pairs, enclosed in curly brackets <code>{}</code>.</p>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 mb-4"><strong>Properties:</strong> Mutable (changeable), does not allow duplicate keys.</p>
                    <div class="bg-purple-50 p-3 rounded-lg text-xs text-purple-900 mb-4">
                        <strong><i class="fa-solid fa-brain mr-1 text-purple-600"></i> Easy Explanation:</strong> Like a real dictionary where you search for a word (Key) to find its meaning (Value).
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-xl p-4 shadow-md font-mono text-xs code-block">
                        <span class="text-sky-300">device</span> = {<br/>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="text-amber-300">"name"</span>: <span class="text-amber-300">"Temperature Sensor"</span>,<br/>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="text-amber-300">"pin"</span>: <span class="text-purple-400">4</span>,<br/>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="text-amber-300">"status"</span>: <span class="text-amber-300">"ON"</span><br/>
                        }<br/>
                        <span class="text-slate-400"># Accessing value using key</span><br/>
                        <span class="text-emerald-400">print</span>(<span class="text-sky-300">device</span>[<span class="text-amber-300">"status"</span>]) <span class="text-slate-500"># Output: ON</span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
